moons.name: moon
moons.alt: Full Moon photograph taken 10-22-2010 from Madison, Alabama, USA.

moons.name: phobos
moons.alt: Color image of Phobos, imaged by the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter on 23 March 2008.

moons.name: deimos
moons.alt: Color-enhanced image of Deimos, a moon of Mars, captured by the HiRISE instrument on the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter on 21 Feb 2009.

moons.name: io
moons.alt: NASA's Galileo spacecraft acquired its highest resolution images of Jupiter's moon Io on 3 July 1999.

moons.name: europa
moons.alt: This image was taken on September 7, 1996, at a range of 677,000 kilometers (417,900 miles) by the solid state imaging television camera onboard the Galileo spacecraft during its second orbit around Jupiter.

moons.name: ganymede
moons.alt: True color image of Ganymede, obtained by the Galileo spacecraft, with enhanced contrast.

moons.name: callisto
moons.alt: Image of Callisto from NASA's Galileo spacecraft. The picture, taken in May 2001, is the only complete global color image of Callisto obtained by Galileo, which has been orbiting Jupiter since December 1995.

moons.name: mimas
moons.alt: In this view captured by NASA's Cassini spacecraft on its closest-ever flyby of Saturn's moon Mimas, large Herschel Crater dominates Mimas, making the moon look like the Death Star in the movie Star Wars.

moons.name: enceladus
moons.alt: NASA's Cassini spacecraft captured this view as it neared icy Enceladus for its closest-ever dive past the moon's active south polar region.

moons.name: tethys
moons.alt: The image was taken in visible light with the Cassini spacecraft narrow-angle camera on April 11, 2015.

moons.name: dione
moons.alt: The image was taken in visible light with the Cassini spacecraft narrow-angle camera on Feb. 8, 2008.

moons.name: rhea
moons.alt: The images in this mosaic were taken with the Cassini spacecraft narrow-angle camera during a close flyby on Nov. 26, 2005.

moons.name: titan
moons.alt: The images were obtained with the Cassini spacecraft wide-angle camera on Jan. 30, 2012.

moons.name: hyperion
moons.alt: Approximately true-color mosaic of Saturn's moon Hyperion. Taken during Cassini's flyby of this lumpy moon on 26th September 2005.

moons.name: iapetus
moons.alt: Iapetus as seen by the Cassini probe.

moons.name: phoebe
moons.alt: Phoebe, as imaged by the Cassini probe.

moons.name: puck
moons.alt: Image taken from Voyager 2 on 24 January 1986.

moons.name: miranda
moons.alt: Uranus' icy moon Miranda is seen in this image from Voyager 2 on January 24, 1986.

moons.name: ariel
moons.alt: This mosaic of the four highest-resolution images of Ariel represents the most detailed Voyager 2 picture of this satellite of Uranus.

moons.name: umbriel
moons.alt: The southern hemisphere of Umbriel displays heavy cratering in this Voyager 2 image, taken Jan. 24, 1986.

moons.name: oberon
moons.alt: This Voyager 2 picture of Oberon is the best the spacecraft acquired of Uranus' outermost moon. The picture was taken shortly after 3:30 a.m. PST on Jan. 24, 1986.

moons.name: triton
moons.alt: Global Color Mosaic of Triton, taken by Voyager 2 in 1989.

moons.name: charon
moons.alt: This image was taken on July 14, 2015, from a range of 46,091 miles (74,176 kilometers). This single color MVIC scan includes no data from other New Horizons imagers or instruments added.
